<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Avena sterilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Elazığ">Elazig</normalizedToken>
is located on the east of Anatolian diagonal, in the skirts of South-Eastern Taurus Mountains (
<bibRefCitation author="Cakilcioglu, U" journalOrPublisher="e-Journal of New World Sciences Academy" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" pagination="232 - 249" refId="B5" refString="Cakilcioglu, U, Tuerkoglu, I, Kuersat, M, 2008. The flora of Citli Lowland (Elazig). e-Journal of New World Sciences Academy 3: 232 - 249" title="The flora of Citli Lowland (Elazig)." volume="3" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Çakılcıoğlu">Cakilcioglu</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), in the Upper Euphrates Region of the Eastern Anatolia Region (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Şengün">Senguen</normalizedToken>
2007). 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Elazığ">Elazig</normalizedToken>
belongs to the Irano-Turanian Plant Geography Region and falls within the B7 grid square (
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, PH" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" refId="B6" refString="Davis, PH, 1965. Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands (Volume 1). Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands (Volume 1)." year="1965">Davis 1965</bibRefCitation>
). The Irano-Turanian Region is confined to Central and East Anatolia. This great region of steppe, mountain steppe and semi-desert is also characterized by the existence of a hypothetical oblique line that runs from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bayburt-Gümüşhane">Bayburt-Guemueshane</normalizedToken>
southwestwardly to Anti-Taurus where it bifurcates with one prong leading to the Amanus and the other to the Cilician Taurus. This line is called &quot;Anatolian Diagonal&quot; (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution map of Allium ekimianum, Allium asperiflorum, Allium sintenisii, Allium erzincanicum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.62.7796.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/84180" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">1</figureCitation>
). The flora of central Anatolia as the western side of the Diagonal is floristically different from the rest of the Irano-Turanian region to the east. According to the plant distribution patterns in eastern Anatolia, many endemics are restricted to part of the Diagonal belt, or extend right along it (
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, PH" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" refId="B6" refString="Davis, PH, 1965. Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands (Volume 1). Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands (Volume 1)." year="1965">Davis 1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, PH" editor="Davis, PH" journalOrPublisher="The Botanical Society of Edinburgh, Edinburgh" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" pagination="15 - 27" refId="B7" refString="Davis, PH, 1971. Distribution patterns in Anatolia with particular reference to endemism. In: Davis, PH, Harper, PC, Hedge, IC, Eds., Plant Life of South-West Asia. The Botanical Society of Edinburgh, Edinburgh: 15 - 27" title="Distribution patterns in Anatolia with particular reference to endemism." volumeTitle="Plant Life of South-West Asia." year="1971">Davis 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="88" type="iucn conservation assessment and justification">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="88">IUCN Conservation Assessment and Justification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="88">
Following the criteria established by IUCN (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland and Cambridge" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" refId="B17" refString="IUCN, 2003. Guidelines for Application of IUCN Red List Criteria at Regional Levels (Version 3). IUCN, Gland and Cambridge" title="Guidelines for Application of IUCN Red List Criteria at Regional Levels (Version 3)" year="2003">IUCN 2003</bibRefCitation>
), an initial provisional assessment of Critically Endangered (CR) (criteria B2a + B2biii) is suggested for this new taxon. This species occurs only in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Elazığ">Elazig</normalizedToken>
University campus area in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Elazığ">Elazig</normalizedToken>
province (East Anatolia) at 1100-1200 m. The area is under subversive people activities such as new constructions of buildings. As a result, the habitat of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eksi, Koyuncu &amp; Oezkan" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium ekimianum" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ekimianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Allium ekimianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly threatened of vanishing by people activities. The area of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eksi, Koyuncu &amp; Oezkan" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium ekimianum" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ekimianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Allium ekimianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occupancy (AOO) is less than 10 km2 with the number of mature individuals which is under reduction and being less than 50.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="88" type="related species">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Related species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eksi, Koyuncu &amp; Oezkan" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium ekimianum" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ekimianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Allium ekimianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miscz ex Grossh" authorityYear="1928" class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium asperiflorum" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asperiflorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Allium asperiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freyn" authorityYear="1892" class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium sintenisii" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sintenisii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Allium sintenisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium erzincanicum" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erzincanicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Allium erzincanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All four species share traits of ovoid bulb, globose to subglobose umbel, campanulate to ovoid perigon, rough outer tepal surfaces, stamens sorter than perigon, ovoid ovary. 
